  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "broadcast-auth-broadcast-double-send",
      "summary": "Authorized state broadcast is emitted twice before returning, creating duplicated fanout work and misleading abstraction semantics.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
        "goseg/leak/broadcast.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`BroadcastToClients` calls `auth.ClientManager.BroadcastAuth(authJson)` twice in the happy-path branch when `HasAuthSession()` is true, while the first return value is already captured and checked after the first call.",
        "There is no conditional branch or policy flag to justify the duplicate call, so callers of the broadcast abstraction cannot predict a single delivery contract."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Use a single authorized broadcast call path (one send + error handling), and if a two-phase strategy is intended, split into explicit calls with distinct payloads and comments or policy parameters.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "ship-config-schema-type-erasure",
      "summary": "Ship config encodes runtime booleans as `any`, forcing ad-hoc conversions and weakening contract boundaries.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/structs/configs.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/collectors_and_mappers.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`UrbitDocker` defines `CustomPierLocation`, `StartramReminder`, `ChopOnUpgrade`, and `DisableShipRestarts` as `any` in the config model.",
        "`collectors_and_mappers.go` and `collectors` logic call `boolSettingWithDefaultTrue` to recover these values at runtime with a default fallback, which masks malformed/mis-typed persisted data.",
        "`urbit_operations.go` and `importer.go` repeatedly assert these fields with type checks (`.(string)` / `.(bool)`), showing callers are compensating for a weak domain contract."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace those `any` fields with explicit typed booleans/string fields in `UrbitDocker` and keep a migration layer in a single unmarshal path that normalizes legacy payloads, so callers consume stable typed config without scattered type assertions.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "leaky_config_schema"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "bootstrap-composition-coupling",
      "summary": "Application startup logic is tightly coupled to concrete subsystems inside `main`, reducing composability and testable abstraction boundaries.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go",
        "goseg/routines/docker.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`main.go` directly calls and wires initialization and loop startup across `auth`, `api`, `importer`, `system`, `routines`, `docker`, `rectify`, and broadcasting modules in one function.",
        "Seam structs are already present (`runtime_seams.go` files) but startup still hardcodes concrete call order and side effects in `main`, so composition is only partial and weak.",
        "Error and recovery behavior is embedded inline in startup sequence, making it harder to substitute policies or defer initialization stages for tests and deployment modes."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a small startup coordinator abstraction (phased startup graph) with explicit dependency ordering and lifecycle status reporting, then move package-specific initialization into registered startup components.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "composition_boundary_gap"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Leaky and weakly typed config domain model forces runtime conversion work across consumers.",
      "Runtime abstractions for startup and orchestration are incomplete or partial, leaving `main` as a tightly coupled composition hub."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "broadcast-auth-broadcast-double-send",
      "ship-config-schema-type-erasure",
      "bootstrap-composition-coupling"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "`broadcast.BroadcastToClients` duplicate send may be an intentional transitional pattern; verify there is no consumer-level expectation for duplicated frames."
